The Serpent - Hardcoded Eng Subs - Sno

Superior thriller adapted from a novel by Ted Lewis (the Get Carter man), seamlessly relocated to contemporary France. It's very much in the neo-Hitchcockian mode, with Yvan Attal as a flawed-but-innocent photographer fending off the vengeful stratagems of a former schoolmate 
It's slick, efficient, tough-nosed film-making, enmeshing our hapless hero more and more tightly in its narrative coils...
